Common.Highlight.Common.Text: On the doorstep of the new airport

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, on behalf of Roberts Jones and the BHL Group, is seeking offers in the form of Expressions of Interest, for the sale of part of The Northern Gateway Site, Badgerys Creek.

This offering is a very rare and limited chance to secure premium Industrial land in a core logistics location within the Western Sydney Aerotropolis; set to be an integrated, world-class economic hub connected by significant road and rail infrastructure. 

Opportunity Highlights 

•	Flexible lots sizes available in the order of 2ha (20,000m2) up to a maximum of 10ha (100,000m2) for purchase. 
•	Core Industrial & Logistics Western Sydney Location 
•	Location on the doorstep of the new Western Sydney Airport and the Commonwealth and NSW governments commitment to the $1.8 billion M12 Motorway expected to be completed in 2025 before the new Western Sydney Airport opens in 2026.
•	The Northern Gateway Site sits within the Penrith LGA and has a Enterprise Zoning (ENT), rezoned in October 2020 via the ‘Aerotropolis SEPP’, allowing for a range of employment and business use.

The subject land is offered for sale via Expressions of Interest closing on Thursday 19th August 2021 4:00pm AEST.  

For further information please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PRIME INDUSTRIAL LAND FOR SALE IN CORE WESTERN SYDNEY LOCATION

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present to the market, located in the most highly sought-after initial precinct within the Western Sydney airport, 205 Lawson Road, Badgerys Creek. 

This opportunity presents itself as a unique opportunity to secure a vast land area of 3.96Ha* adjoining the Western Sydney airport. 

205 Lawson Road, Badgerys Creek presents the following key attributes:

- A well-exposed, and high profile 3.96Ha* parcel in the Badgerys Creek Precinct 
- Earmarked to be rezoned in Q3/Q4 of 2020 to flexible mixed use/employment
- Adjoining the Western Sydney airport with direct access via Pitt Street* located 200m* from the subject property
- As per the Western Sydney airport report 2019, the Badgerys Creek precinct permits defence and aerospace, advanced manufacturing activity, high technology industry, airport supporting development, local retail, Aerotropolis enabling industries, modernised resource recovery industries, light industrial, social infrastructure.
- Located within proximity to the Mamre Road precinct where Amazon has most recently committed a 20-year lease across 200,000sqm*
- Surrounding government infrastructure totalling over $5.25 billion which will contribute towards the M12, North South Rail and Western Sydney airport. 

205 Lawson Road will be offered to the market via an expressions of interest campaign closing on the 17th of September at 3pm. 

For more information please contact the exclusive agents listed.

CBRE is pleased to present 10 Martin Road, Badgerys Creek to the market for sale via an on-site Public Auction. This terrific land holding is an extremely rare opportunity and should not be overlooked for your next investment.

10 Martin Road, Badgerys Creek boasts the follow key attributes:
- Super prime corner land holding in one of Sydney’s most in-demand locations and along the major arterial road, Elizabeth Drive 
- The total site area is 5 acres of prime land in a future growth suburb (20,300sqm)* - perfect for future redevelopment 
- Earmarked for future 'Flexible Employment' land under government and state planning rezoning
- The property benefits from proximity to all current and future amenity; Western Sydney Airport, Mirvac Industrial Estate, Sydney Science Park, M12/M9 Motorway, BHL Materplan Site, and existing M7 Motorway 
- The property is located in the middle of one of Australia’s largest growth and government funded infrastructure pockets of the Western Parkland City and is moments from the future Western Sydney Airport; a $5.3 billion-dollar commitment from the Federal Government. 

The Public Auction will be held on-site on Saturday, 20th October 2018 at 10:00am. 

To discuss the property in more detail, please be in contact with the CBRE team.
